==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moratory
<hw>Mor"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>moratorius</ets> delaying, fr. <ets>morari</ets> to delay.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to delay; esp., designating a law passed, as in a
time of financial panic, to postpone or delay for a period the time at
which notes, bills of exchange, and other obligations, shall mature or
become due.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moravian</ent>⟦br⟧
